title: Vanessa Hudgens and Ashley Tisdale Give Us the High School Musical Duet We Always Wanted
text:
Vanessa Hudgens and Ashley Tisdale Singing "Ex's & Oh's" Vanessa Hudgens and Ashley Tisdale Give Us the High School Musical Duet We Always Wanted January 3, 2017 by Ryan Roschke 330 Shares 
It's been over a decade since the first High School Musical movie debuted on the Disney channel, and in the time since, the cast has spiraled off into wildly different directions . But if we learned anything during our time with the crew, it's that once you're a Wildcat, you're always a Wildcat. Coming off the epic 10-year reunion in 2016 , the latest mini get-together featured the two biggest starlets from the series, Ashley Tisdale and Vanessa Hudgens . Tisdale welcomed her former costar to her YouTube channel to sing a sweet cover of "Ex's & Oh's." Considering how the two never had a duet in the HSM movies, it's like we're getting the pairing we never knew we needed . . . until now. Related:
